DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(91)90012-U
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/002219969190012U
AB  - This paper shows that under external increasing returns to scale and a strictly concave production possibilities frontier the shadow price of foreign exchange in the presence of a tariff is the same as that in an economy with purely constant returns to scale. However, with a quota or a voluntary export restraint, this shadow price is, in general, quite different from that in a purely constant returns to scale economy.
