AB  - This paper develops a two-step decision model of the multinational enterprise under foreign demand uncertainty, where international investment is undertaken ex ante and international trade ex post. It demonstrates that efficient capital utilization is achieved even under uncertainty regardless of the attitudes of the multinational enterprise toward risk, but the risk-averse multinational enterprise may invest and produce less in both home and host countries than the risk-neutral one. The paper furthermore reports some of the comparative statics results.
