DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(91)90005-Q
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/002219969190005Q
AB  - This paper derives the necessary conditions for an intertemporal optimization problem faced by an international investor who can enter forward contracts of several maturity dates and simultaneously borrow in domestic money markets. The model parameters are estimated and the overidentifying restrictions are tested using Hansen's proposed GMM technique. The restrictions are strongly rejected when forward premia are used as instruments. The risk-neutral specification is rejected when expenditures on non-durables and services are used as the consumption measure. Possible explanations for these rejections are provided.
